🧠 What is Routing?

**Routing** means:

👉 Deciding how the server responds to different URLs (endpoints)

Example:

```text id="t4rqgq"
/ → Home Page  
/about → About Page  
/api/users → Users Data  
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Routing in HTTP Module (Manual Way)

Node.js HTTP module requires manual routing.

---

Example

```javascript id="bapb1r"
const http = require("http");

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {

  if (req.url === "/") {
    res.write("Home Page");
  } 
  else if (req.url === "/about") {
    res.write("About Page");
  } 
  else if (req.url === "/api") {
    res.write(JSON.stringify({ message: "API" }));
  } 
  else {
    res.write("404 Not Found");
  }

  res.end();
});

server.listen(3000);
```

